# webOS/LG Smart TV Telemetry & Ad Blocklist (Pi-hole/Hosts format)
# Author: athimannil
# 
# This hosts file is intended to block tracking, telemetry, and advertisements on LG webOS Smart TVs
# and common Smart TV platforms, including some YouTube ad domains.
# 
# Usage: Import this file into your Pi-hole, AdGuard, or place directly in your system's hosts file.
# Each domain below resolves to 0.0.0.0, effectively blocking unwanted connections.
#
# Last updated: 2025-11-09

# LG Device Telemetry
0.0.0.0 eic.lgtviot.com
0.0.0.0 eic-connect-client.lgthinq.com
0.0.0.0 eic.commonpush.lgtviot.com
0.0.0.0 eic.lgchhomeapp.lgtvcommon.com
0.0.0.0 prd-api.lgthinq.com
0.0.0.0 lgsmartad.lgtvsdp.com
0.0.0.0 us.ad.lgsmartad.com
0.0.0.0 de.ad.lgsmartad.com
0.0.0.0 eu.ad.lgsmartad.com
0.0.0.0 config.lgtvsdp.com
0.0.0.0 tracking.lgtvsdp.com

# LG Remote / Control Ads
0.0.0.0 ngfts.lge.com
0.0.0.0 snc.lge.com
0.0.0.0 lge.com.edgesuite.net
0.0.0.0 ad.lgappstv.com
0.0.0.0 aic-ngfts.lge.com

# YouTube Ads Blocklist
0.0.0.0 s.youtube.com
0.0.0.0 ads.youtube.com
